The R617 to Underberg/Boston has been blocked by illegal protesters. uMngeni Municipality Mayor Christopher Pappas on Wednesday morning said all authorities have been notified and will attend accordingly. Pappas said the cause of the “illegal protests” is not yet fully known. ALSO READ | Umgungundlovu residents urged to pay for services or face not receiving them “Information received is that a silver Avanza is driving around Mpophomeni telling people to protest the water-related issues. There is also information about people protesting illegal electricity disconnections,” he said. Motorists have been advised to avoid the R617. *This is a developing story